Summary: Describes the location and basic structure of the Debugger panel in Godot.
The Debugger panel, containing many of Godot's debugging tools, is located at the bottom of the screen. Click on "Debugger" to open it. The panel is divided into several tabs, each dedicated to a specific debugging task.
